<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-21T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.124a/87: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reber</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-21T16:00:00-04:00">August 21, 1930—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>70. From Surgeon General Cumming to Surgeon H. F. Smith: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>In answer to your telegram dated August 20, in which your recall
                                    was suggested, it is advisable for you to continue on the
                                    present detail until the financial reorganization has been
                                    completed in October. You are, meanwhile, authorized in your
                                    discretion to visit at expense of the service neighboring West
                                    African countries to observe the local activities for the
                                    control of quarantinable diseases and to return not later than
                                    the latter part of September to Monrovia.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>